.TH "splice_from_pipe_next" 9 "splice_from_pipe_next" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
splice_from_pipe_next \- wait for some data to splice from
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" splice_from_pipe_next
.BI "(struct pipe_inode_info *pipe "  ","
.BI "struct splice_desc *sd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pipe" 12
pipe to splice from
.IP "sd" 12
information about the splice operation
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function will wait for some data and return a positive
value (one) if pipe buffers are available.  It will return zero
or -errno if no more data needs to be spliced.
